<subSubSection pageId="46" pageNumber="103" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="46.[151,1437,526,2036]" pageId="46" pageNumber="103">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,286,526,551]" pageId="46" pageNumber="103">Etymology.</emphasis>
The species is named after the indigenous Guaraní people. The word 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Sassi" authorityYear="2018" box="[1067,1156,527,550]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Metallactus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="46" pageNumber="103" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="guarani">
<emphasis box="[1067,1156,527,550]" italics="true" pageId="46" pageNumber="103">guarani</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a latinized noun in the nominative singular, standing in apposition to the generic name (art. 11.9.1.2. I.C.Z.N., 4th edition).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
